title: President-elect of the United States
added: A group of 300,000 Black women, [[Alpha Kappa Alpha]] wanted to witness the history, where Harris became the first Black woman Vice President. The organization’s president Glenda Baskin Glover said that Black women had always been a cornerstone of Democratic politics, where Harris’ win is a reward. Due to Covid restrictions, AKA planned to virtually hang-out over zoom and cheer Harris on her inauguration ceremony.<ref>{{cite_web|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/black-women-ready-to-virtually-cheer-on-kamala-harriss-inauguration-11610895600|title=Black Women Ready to Virtually Cheer On Kamala Harris’s Inauguration|accessdate=17 January 2021|website=The Wall Street Journal}}</ref>

title: President-elect of the United States
deleted: During the presidential transition period, the president-elect's [[running mate]] is known as the vice president-elect.

title: President-elect of the United States
